        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 20 at 6:08PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 608 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Buckhead, or near
Madison, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, up to penny sized hail and frequent
cloud to ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Greensboro, Union Point, White Plains, Siloam, Buckhead, Phoenix,
Reynolds at Lake Oconee, Liberty, Veazey, Robinson, Harmony,
Greshamville, Rockville, Parks Mill, Carey, and Swords.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
